10:11:19  Failure in model assets (models\asset_tracking\assets.sql)
10:11:19    ('42000', "[42000] [Microsoft][ODBC Driver 17 for SQL Server][SQL Server]The statement failed. Column 'Picture' has a data type that cannot participate in a columnstore index. (35343) (SQLMoreResults)")

Your dbt model is failing because SQL Server is trying to create a columnstore index, but the column:
=====================   ===================     ==============    ====================   ========================    ==========================================
=====================   ===================     ==============    ====================   ========================    =======================================


Picture

has a datatype that is not supported in columnstore indexes.

✅ Why this happens

In SQL Server, columnstore indexes do NOT support some datatypes like:

image
text
ntext
xml
varchar(max)
nvarchar(max)
varbinary(max)
FILESTREAM columns

Most likely your Picture column is one of these types.

✅ What dbt is doing

The SQL Server dbt adapter (dbt-sqlserver) often creates tables with:

CLUSTERED COLUMNSTORE INDEX

by default for performance.

But SQL Server rejects it because of the Picture column.

✅ Solutions
Option 1 (Recommended) → Exclude the Picture column

If you don't need the image/binary column:

select
    asset_id,
    asset_name,
    created_at
from source_table

Avoid selecting Picture.

Option 2 → Disable columnstore index in dbt

Inside your model:

{{
  config(
    materialized='table',
    as_columnstore=false
  )
}}

select * from ...

This is usually the best fix when you need that column.

✅ Full example
{{
  config(
    materialized='table',
    as_columnstore=false
  )
}}

select *
from {{ source('asset_tracking', 'assets') }}
✅ Why this works

Setting:

as_columnstore=false

tells dbt:

"Create a normal heap/rowstore table instead of a columnstore table."

Then SQL Server allows the Picture column.

✅ Best practice

For tables containing:

images
PDFs
JSON blobs
XML
large text/binary columns

avoid columnstore indexes.

Columnstore is best for:

analytics
numeric data
aggregations
fact tables
✅ Most likely root cause in your case

Your source table probably has:

Picture VARBINARY(MAX)

or

Picture IMAGE

which SQL Server cannot place into a columnstore index.

✅ Final fix

Add this at the top of assets.sql:

{{
  config(
    materialized='table',
    as_columnstore=false
  )
}}

Then run again:

dbt run -s assets